[Patient] "How much water should I drink each day?"
[Educator] "Try to limit your fluid intake to about 2 liters a day."
[Patient] "What about other beverages like juice or soda?"
[Educator] "It's best to stick to water and avoid sugary drinks that can worsen fluid retention."
[Patient] "Can I have coffee or tea?"
[Educator] "Limit caffeine intake as it can also contribute to fluid retention."
[Patient] "Should I track my fluid intake throughout the day?"
[Educator] "Yes, keeping a log can help you monitor and control your fluid intake."
[Patient] "What about eating foods with high water content?"
[Educator] "It's okay to include fruits and vegetables with high water content in your diet."
[Patient] "How do I know if I'm drinking too much fluid?"
[Educator] "Watch for signs like swelling, shortness of breath, or sudden weight gain."
[Patient] "What should I do if I notice these symptoms?"
[Educator] "Contact your healthcare provider immediately for guidance on managing your symptoms."